A POLICE officer has been bust and charged with murder and attempted murder. The victims of the incident at a tavern in Kagiso, Mogale City, on Friday 27 January were allegedly shot while trying to protect the suspect’s girlfriend while he assaulted her. The tavern manager sadly died of his wounds while a security guard is in hospital fighting for his life. Gauteng police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Mavela Masondo told Daily Sun the sergeant (41) was bust in the early hours of Saturday morning, 28 January. Masondo said the tavern manager was certified dead on arrival at a hospital while the guard was in a serious but stable condition. “It’s reported that the suspect arrived at the tavern and found his girlfriend, who he assaulted. The tavern manager and the security guard intervened,” he said. You must be SIGNED IN to comment! Masondo said it was alleged that the cop left and came back with a firearm before shooting both victims. “The victims were taken to a local medical care centre,” he said. The cop is expected to appear in the Kagiso Magistrates Court on Monday 30 January.